I made this about a month ago. I used the bone in breast as recommended in the recipe, as the bones add more flavor. I removed the skin before browning. I didn't have sundried tomatoes in oil, so I just used regular sundried tomates I buy in bulk. They are soft and moist and I minced them then added EVOO in with the bread crumbs,garlic and some pepper until crumbs held together, but weren't greasy. I also lowered the oven temperature to 350 and still found you had to watch for burning and tent with foil last half of baking or so. Checked after 25 minutes and put in for another 5, depends on size/thickness of breast. Also used stainless ovenproof skillet to brown breasts, topped with crumbs, put in oven right in skillet. Works great, less cleanup. I use this method for alot of different smaller cuts of meat, pork loins, small roasts. Hubby loved it, lots of flavor, meat very moist. Am making again tonight and serving with roasted fennel with pinenuts and brown rice.

