I made this dish last night for some new friends that I was hoping to impress - and it came out GREAT! I read the other reviews and paid attention to how dry the crust mixture turned out. I cooked the breasts in about 4 tbsp of the sun dried tomato oil and in addition to adding the oil to the mixture as directed, I also added the leftover juices/oil from the pan I cooked the chicken in. This made the mixture very moist and it came out as kind of a stuffing consistency and was wonderful! My husband says this is a keeper for sure! It is VERY important not to overcook the chicken. I did skinless, boneless breasts and the 'crust' kept them moist and tender. I also 'made' the bread crumbs myself from fresh french bread, which I think made a difference. Our guests raved and insisted I send them the recipe - delicious!

