Rating: 3
Very good recipe which allows for some minor modifications and creativity. I would like to add that the cook from 1/5 likely thinks Chef Boyardee is representative of Italian cooking. True Italy Italian cooking is far different than what is found in the US. The larger emigrant sending areas to the US -- Sicily being one -- cook much differently than in Northern Italy. I grew up in South Philly and have traveled extensively in Italy. Not the same cuisine. One is not necessarily better than the other -- just different. People get so hung up with following (what they believe) to be ultimate cooking rules. Live a little!

